# Sales Report Rules

**Every uploaded or replaced sales CSV must follow these rules** — bundled seed (`data/reports/Sales-Report.csv`), Data Analyst upload, and API `POST /api/reports`.

## Top 20 products — hide only, never exclude from totals

Excluded SKUs are **hidden from Top 20 products** (Sales Dashboard, voice, chat, Data Analyst) but **must still count** in total revenue, store rankings, departments, vendors, margins, and all other aggregates.

### Exclusion rules (match on SKU # or Item #)

| Rule | Reason |
|------|--------|
| `ITEM` | Placeholder / custom order / special order lines |
| `250000` | CBE recycling fee |
| Starts with `MLB-` | Mulberry lifetime / care plans |
| `JVS-200940` | Watch battery service (repair, not product) |
| `217365`, `217286`, `159004` | Legacy excluded SKUs |

### Implementation (do not bypass on upload)

- **Single source of truth:** `isExcludedTopProductSku()` + `EXCLUDED_TOP_PRODUCT_SKUS` in `src/lib/utils.ts`
- **On every summarize/upload:** `rankProducts()` in `src/lib/reports/vendor-pos.ts` skips excluded SKUs
- **On every display:** `filterTopProductSkus()` in sales page, `TopProductsTable`, voice, assistant, context builder

When adding exclusions, update `src/lib/utils.ts` only. Never filter excluded rows out of `periodRows` or revenue totals.

## Bundled default report

- File: `data/reports/Sales-Report.csv`
- Seeded via `src/lib/reports/store.ts`; app refreshes `.data/reports/` when the file changes
